verbose_text: Cranial MRI undertaken at just over 36 hr of age demonstrated a diffusely abnormal signal intensity of the entire supratenterial white matter and decreased cortical folding for her age (XREF_FIG A), as well as of the brainstem (XREF_FIG B) and cerebellar white matter.
